n**根因分析**：shippingservice 的端口配置存在问题，导致 frontend 服务无法建立到 shippingservice 的 gRPC 连接，从而影响了订单处理流程。\n\n--- Metric Agent Findings ---\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\n    \"client_error_ratio\",\n    \"error_ratio\",\n    \"rrt_max\",\n    \"rrt\",\n    \"node_memory_usage_rate\",\n    \"node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes\",\n    \"pod_cpu_usage\",\n    \"request\",\n    \"response\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"shippingservice-2\",\n      \"reason\": \"异常原因：client_error_ratio 和 error_ratio 显著增加，且 request 和 response 指标异常。\",\n      \"evidence\": \"client_error_ratio 和 error_ratio 的 p99 值从 0.0 增加到 30.0，变化率为 2.0。\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"currencyservice-1\",\n      \"reason\": \"异常原因：rrt_max 显著增加，表明服务响应时间变长。\",\n      \"evidence\": \"rrt_max 的中位数从 6691.0 增加到 7259.0，变化率为 0.0814。\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-04\",\n      \"reason\": \"异常原因：node_memory_usage_rate 下降，但 node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes 也下降，可能内存泄漏或系统问题。\",\n      \"evidence\": \"node_memory_usage_rate 的中位数从 34.39 下降到 29.54，变化率为 0.1517。\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"paymentservice-1\",\n      \"reason\": \"异常原因：rrt_max 和 rrt 显著增加，表明服务性能下降。\",\n      \"evidence\": \"rrt_max 的中位数从 2529.0 增加到 3423.0，变化率为 0.3004。\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n--- Trace Agent Findings ---\nBased on the trace data analysis, I can now provide a detailed root cause analysis for the fault. Let me examine the key findings from the trace data.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\"error_ratio\", \"rrt_max\", \"checkoutservice->shippingservice\", \"frontend->checkoutservice\", \"cartservice->redis\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"shippingservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"error_ratio\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Multiple connection refused errors (status 14) from checkoutservice to shippingservice: 'connection error: dial tcp 10.233.27.213:50051: connect: connection refused' - indicates shippingservice is completely unavailable\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"cartservice-redis\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\", \n      \"evidence\": \"Redis HMSET operation latency increased from 1.66s to 20.83s (12.6x increase), cartservice GetCart from 2.55s to 32.05s (12.6x increase) - severe performance degradation\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"error_ratio\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Checkout failures propagating upstream with status 13 errors: 'shipping quote failure: failed to get shipping quote' due to shippingservice unavailability\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Key Findings Analysis:**\n\n1. **Primary Root Cause**: The shippingservice is completely unavailable, evidenced by multiple \"connection refused\" errors from checkoutservice. This is the starting point of the failure cascade.\n\n2. **Secondary Issue**: Redis performance degradation affecting cartservice operations, with HMSET operations showing 12.6x latency increase.\n\n3. **Error Propagation**: \n   - shippingservice unavailability → checkoutservice failures → frontend 500 errors\n   - The checkout process is failing due to inability to get shipping quotes\n\n4. **Impact Scope**: The fault affects the entire checkout flow, with frontend services receiving HTTP 500 errors when attempting to place orders.\n\nThe trace data clearly shows a service dependency chain failure originating from the shippingservice being unreachable.\n\n--- Previous Consensus Decision ---\nNo consensus yet", "metric_analysis_findings": "See Log Findings for Full Context", "trace_analysis_findings": "See Log Findings for Full Context", "consensus_decision": "AGREED", "current_hypothesis": "shippingservice-2 is the root cause due to port configuration error causing connection refused errors"}
